        <abstract> 
<p>He has examined <hi rend="italic">Hoya</hi> flowers with Bentham and Oliver, but they are not satisfied about the five processes alternating with the sepals. [See <hi rend="italic">Forms of flowers</hi>, pp. 331–2.] Sends specimens of plants.</p> 
            <p>Babington’s surprise at JDH’s advocacy of Darwinian views at Norwich [BAAS meeting].</p> 
<p>Criticism of the behaviour of the trustees of the British Museum [in the <hi rend="italic">Challenger</hi> affair].</p> 
        </abstract>
